Dennis Naku, Port Harcourt The Rivers State Independent Electoral Commission has fixed 17th April, 2021, for local government elections. The RSIEC Chairman, Justice George Omereji (retd.), said this during a stakeholders’ meeting at the commission’s headquarters in Port Harcourt. While unveiling the guidelines and timetable for the election, Omereji urged the various political party leaders and their supporters to abide by the rules of the game. He said, “There shall be local government council elections on Saturday, the 17th day of April 2021 in all the 23 local government areas of the guidelines in which A, one councillor shall be elected in each ward. “B. A chairman and vice chairman shall be elected for each of the local government areas. I humbly appeal to all politicians aspiring to contest for the positions to do so in a civil and discipline manner. “You are expected to play by the rules. The rules that guidelines are set for the good of all. They are not intended or skewed against any party or individuals. We all have a collective responsibility to consolidate our nascent democracy experience.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com   